article.headline: Oral Roberts 65, W. Illinois 46
article.story: TULSA, Okla. (AP) -- Caleb Green scored 13 of his team-high 22 points in the first half to spark Oral Roberts past Western Illinois 65-46 in a Mid-Continent Conference opener for both teams on Thursday night. Green was 8-of-13 from the field and 6-of-8 on free throws. He also had seven rebounds. Moses Ehambe came off the bench to add 13 points, including three treys, for ORU (8-7, 1-0 MidCon). Western Illinois shot 26 percent (17-of-65) from the field compared with 44 percent (23-of-52) for ORU. The Leathernecks missed their first 12 shots and never led. Sammy Hunter scored 14 points to lead the Leathernecks (4-10, 0-1), who have lost nine of their last 11 games. ORU, which led 31-20 at intermission, opened the second half with a 13-4 run to break the game open. The Golden Eagles' biggest lead was at 51-28 with 8:42 left. Western Illinois cut its deficit to 60-45 with 2:51 left, but Ehambe sank two free throws and a trey to repel the Leathernecks' comeback bid. The Golden Eagles outrebounded the Leathernecks 42-37. Green had six points in the first six minutes as ORU jumped to a 7-0 lead. A basket by David Jackson cut the ORU lead to 10-8 midway through the first half. After the teams exchanged baskets, ORU went on a 12-0 run that included six points by Green, who later made two free throws to end the half.
